<div id="show-message-chrome-extensions-toolbar" class="hidden show-message">
    <div class="box">
        <div class="box-inner">
            <p>
                Google Chrome hides extensions by default but you can use the extensions <span class="no-wrap">menu <img src="/images/messages/chrome/puzzle.png?version=2025.1.1.0" width="18" height="18" class="icon icon-chrome-puzzle" alt></span> in the upper right of Chrome to enable the <span class="no-wrap">pin <img src="/images/messages/chrome/pin.png?version=2025.1.1.0" width="18" height="18" class="icon icon-chrome-pin" alt></span> option for Pluma.
            </p>

            <p>
                The above procedure will allow the Pluma status <span class="no-wrap">icon <img src="/images/messages/chrome/status.png?version=2025.1.1.0" width="18" height="18" class="icon" alt></span> to be visible and enable one-click access.
            </p>

            <p>
                <input class="button show-message-dismiss" data-id="show-message-chrome-extensions-toolbar" type="button" value="Continue">
            </p>
        </div><!-- box-inner -->
    </div><!-- box -->
</div><!-- show-message-chrome-extensions-toolbar -->

