<div id="show-message-guide" class="hidden show-message">
    <div class="box">
        <div class="box-inner">
            <p>
                If this is your first experience with Pluma, you should view the <a class="page" href="/page/<js>write(theme)</js>/<js>write(icon)</js>/guide.html#smooth-overview">guide</a> which includes an overview, usage instructions, limitations, and other information.
            </p>

            <p>
                If you are in a rush, the most important thing to know is that once a page is in edit mode, you must hold down a modifier key like ALT when clicking a link, if you actually want to follow that link, and not edit it.
            </p>

            <p>
                <input class="button show-message-dismiss" data-id="show-message-guide" type="button" value="Continue">
            </p>
        </div><!-- box-inner -->
    </div><!-- box -->
</div><!-- show-message-guide -->